ning, and that exploring the history of their letters offers a profound insight into their subjectivity and agency over time.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 0aLetter writingzEuropexHistory. 0aWomenzEuropexSocial conditionsxHistory. 4aDiachronic. 4aGender and Sexuality Studies. 4aHistory, Art History, and Archaeology. 4aMedia Studies. 4aSociology and Social History. 7aHISTORY / Medieval.2bisacsh  aEpistolarity, Gender, Family, Women.1 aGarrioch, David, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aJames, Carolyn, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAmsterdam University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023z978311102374808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishz978311131929208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023z9783111318912oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2023 Englishz978311131913108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2023z9783111318189oZDB-23-DEG40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9789048556427zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9789048556427/original  a978-3-11-102374-8 Amsterdam University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023b2023  a978-3-11-131913-1 EBOOK PACKAGE History 2023 Englishb2023  a978-3-11-131929-2 EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishb2023  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DEGb2023  aZDB-23-DGGb2023  aZDB-23-GOA